Message:
@Steve I definitely have a bias towards small teams that are free to engage in higher-order thoughts, and I think that bias is probably showing pretty clear in this discussion lol

I'm not sure I believe in an average developer... I've been surprised sometimes at who has taught me things throughout my journey, and I think all anyone needs is the right situation and a bit of time to become exceptional. But hey, I'm an optimist and an idealist, a dangerous combination :)

@Paul agreed, it is certainly more of an oblong shape... and probably a bit irregular for most :) Oh, I think my brain is wavering a bit here between business insights and code insights; I think at a master level, business insights are certainly more frequent than code-level / structural insights.

It's kind of what I love about the fundamental aspects of Agile, that we expect developers to have business insights, to integrate with the business. Software becomes a tool for a higher purpose, rather than a purpose unto itself. Now we can get all meta and start talking about tool building :) lol
